cdx6500PPCTIBM2260PortTable.name: cdx6500PPCTIBM2260PortTable
cdx6500PPCTIBM2260PortTable.description: A list of IBM2260 Port configuration entries.

cdx6500PPCTIBM2260PortEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTIBM2260PortEntry
cdx6500PPCTIBM2260PortEntry.description: An IBM2260 Configuration Table entry. Each entry contains the configuration parameters for a single IBM2260 port.

cdx6500IBM2260CfgPortNumber.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgPortNumber
cdx6500IBM2260CfgPortNumber.description: The port number corresponding to this port.

cdx6500IBM2260CfgPadType.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgPadType
cdx6500IBM2260CfgPadType.description: Indicates whether the port is functioning as a Terminal PAD (TPAD) or a Host PAD (HPAD).

cdx6500IBM2260CfgPortSpeed.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgPortSpeed
cdx6500IBM2260CfgPortSpeed.description: This is the speed of the port in bits per second, when using internal clocking.

cdx6500IBM2260CfgConnType.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgConnType
cdx6500IBM2260CfgConnType.description: Specify the control signal handshake required for a connection to be made to this port: simp - simple, no control signals required. simpa - CTS follows RTS, but no control signals required.

cdx6500IBM2260CfgNumDevice.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgNumDevice
cdx6500IBM2260CfgNumDevice.description: Specifies the number of IBM2260 stations on this line.

cdx6500IBM2260CfgServiceTimer.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgServiceTimer
cdx6500IBM2260CfgServiceTimer.description: The Service Timer specifies the interval of time in seconds between periodic servicing. Such servicing includes intervals between attempts to establish network connections, intervals between attempts in TPAD to poll terminals that previously failed to respond, and in HPAD this timer is also used to detect host inactivity (i.e. when the host stops polling the station(s)).

cdx6500IBM2260CfgThreshCtr.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgThreshCtr
cdx6500IBM2260CfgThreshCtr.description: Indicates number of consecutive errors that can occur before a station is considered down.

cdx6500IBM2260CfgRespTimeout.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgRespTimeout
cdx6500IBM2260CfgRespTimeout.description: Specifies the amount of time in msec the PAD allows a terminal, printer or host to respond. As a result, the TPAD may re-transmit the previous message or abort the current procedure. The HPAD aborts the current procedure as though EOT was received, allowing this HPAD station to disconnect it's SVC if the host malfunctions. An HPAD with a response timeout shorter than the hosts ability to respond may result in Inbound Errors.

cdx6500IBM2260CfgPortSubAddr.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgPortSubAddr
cdx6500IBM2260CfgPortSubAddr.description: Calls addressed to this node and with this subaddress will be routed to this port.

cdx6500IBM2260CfgPortOpt.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgPortOpt
cdx6500IBM2260CfgPortOpt.description: Select options on this IBM2260 port as follows: NONE - No option specified ORG - Originate calls from this port ACK - DSP End-to-End Acknowledgements are to be used Any combination of above specified by summing (e.g. ORG+ACK).

cdx6500IBM2260CfgRestConnDest.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgRestConnDest
cdx6500IBM2260CfgRestConnDest.description: All calls originating from this port will be routed to the destination specified in this parameter, irrespective of route selection table entries. For example, to route calls to port 1, use P1. To route calls to port 2, station 4, use P2S4. Blank this field to disable this function.

cdx6500IBM2260CfgBillRec.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgBillRec
cdx6500IBM2260CfgBillRec.description: This controls whether billing (accounting) records will be created for calls on this port.

cdx6500IBM2260CfgElectricalInterfaceType.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgElectricalInterfaceType
cdx6500IBM2260CfgElectricalInterfaceType.description: Specify the Electrical Interface Type: V.24 - V.24 Electrical Interface Type V.35 - V.35 Electrical Interface Type V.36 - V.36 Electrical Interface Type X.21 - X.21 Electrical Interface Type Note: Changing this parameter requires manual settings on SWITCH1: Interface SW1-1 SW1-2 SW1-3 SW1-4 SW1-5 SW1-6 SW1-7 SW1-8 V.24 ON ON ON ON ON OFF OFF OFF V.35,V.36,X.21 OFF OFF OFF OFF OFF ON ON ON

cdx6500IBM2260CfgV24ElectricalInterfaceO.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500IBM2260CfgV24ElectricalInterfaceO.description: Specify the Pin 22 option: RI - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Ring Indicator output signal TM - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Test Mode input signal

cdx6500IBM2260CfgHighSpeedElectricalInte.name: cdx6500IBM2260CfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500IBM2260CfgHighSpeedElectricalInte.description: Specify the cable type: NONE - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with straight through cable XOVER - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with crossover adapter cable

cdx6500PPSTIBM2260PortTable.name: cdx6500PPSTIBM2260PortTable
cdx6500PPSTIBM2260PortTable.description: A list of IBM2260 Port statistics.

cdx6500PPSTIBM2260PortEntry.name: cdx6500PPSTIBM2260PortEntry
cdx6500PPSTIBM2260PortEntry.description: An IBM2260 Statistics Table entry. Each entry contains the statistics for a single IBM2260 port.

cdx6500IBM2260StatPortStatus.name: cdx6500IBM2260StatPortStatus
cdx6500IBM2260StatPortStatus.description: Operational Status of the port. The different operational statuses are: UP : At least 1 station is responding to polls. DOWN : None of the stations are responding to polls. DISABLED : The port is disabled by the user.

cdx6500IBM2260StatPortSpeed.name: cdx6500IBM2260StatPortSpeed
cdx6500IBM2260StatPortSpeed.description: The measured port speed in bits per second.

cdx6500IBM2260StatPortUtilin.name: cdx6500IBM2260StatPortUtilin
cdx6500IBM2260StatPortUtilin.description: The amount of the port's bandwidth that is being utilized; because IBM2260 is a half-duplex protocol the utilization is calculated as the sum of the receive and transmit utilization.

cdx6500IBM2260StatPortUtilOut.name: cdx6500IBM2260StatPortUtilOut
cdx6500IBM2260StatPortUtilOut.description: The amount of the port's bandwidth that is being utilized; because IBM2260 is a half-duplex protocol the utilization is calculated as the sum of the receive and transmit utilization.

cdx6500IBM2260StatParityErrors.name: cdx6500IBM2260StatParityErrors
cdx6500IBM2260StatParityErrors.description: The number of character parity errors counted by the I/O driver.

cdx6500IBM2260StatOverrunErrors.name: cdx6500IBM2260StatOverrunErrors
cdx6500IBM2260StatOverrunErrors.description: The number of received character overruns counted by the I/O driver.

cdx6500IBM2260StatFramingErrors.name: cdx6500IBM2260StatFramingErrors
cdx6500IBM2260StatFramingErrors.description: The number of asynchronous chracters received which violated the character framing of start and stop bits. Note, this statistic is only valid if the port is configured for ASYNC line interface.

cdx6500IBM2260StatBCCErrors.name: cdx6500IBM2260StatBCCErrors
cdx6500IBM2260StatBCCErrors.description: The number of BCC errors counted by the I/O driver.

cdx6500IBM2260StatNoResponse.name: cdx6500IBM2260StatNoResponse
cdx6500IBM2260StatNoResponse.description: The number of times the response timer has expired.

cdx6500IBM2260StatCharInTotal.name: cdx6500IBM2260StatCharInTotal
cdx6500IBM2260StatCharInTotal.description: Total number of chracters received to present.

cdx6500IBM2260StatCharOutTotal.name: cdx6500IBM2260StatCharOutTotal
cdx6500IBM2260StatCharOutTotal.description: Total number of chracters transmitted to present.

cdx6500IBM2260StatCharInSecond.name: cdx6500IBM2260StatCharInSecond
cdx6500IBM2260StatCharInSecond.description: Average number of characters received to present.

cdx6500IBM2260StatCharOutSecond.name: cdx6500IBM2260StatCharOutSecond
cdx6500IBM2260StatCharOutSecond.description: Average number of characters transmitted to present.

cdx6500IBM2260StatMsgRetran.name: cdx6500IBM2260StatMsgRetran
cdx6500IBM2260StatMsgRetran.description: Number of messages retransmitted due to NAKs or timeouts to present.

cdx6500SPCTIBM2260StationTable.name: cdx6500SPCTIBM2260StationTable
cdx6500SPCTIBM2260StationTable.description: All of the configuration parameters relevant to the IBM2260 Station table.

cdx6500SPCTIBM2260StationEntry.name: cdx6500SPCTIBM2260StationEntry
cdx6500SPCTIBM2260StationEntry.description: A row of IBM2260 station configuration parameters.

cdx6500IBM2260sType.name: cdx6500IBM2260sType
cdx6500IBM2260sType.description: single - configures a single station addressable by the ADDR1-ADDR2 address pair. group - configures a group of stations addressable by the ADDR1 address character, but ADDR2 is assumed to be 40H, 41H, 42H and 43H. This type is intended for support of DataTroll devices. NOTE: `group' Station should not be used when the BSC3270-IBM2260 protocol Interoperation is being used.

cdx6500IBM2260sStationAddr1.name: cdx6500IBM2260sStationAddr1
cdx6500IBM2260sStationAddr1.description: This is the first byte of this Station's address. The Station address consists of two hexadecimal digits. The valid range for a digit is: 20-7F;

cdx6500IBM2260sStationAddr2.name: cdx6500IBM2260sStationAddr2
cdx6500IBM2260sStationAddr2.description: This is the second byte of this Station's address. The Station address consists of two hexadecimal digits. The valid range for a digit is: 20-7F

cdx6500IBM2260sCallMnem.name: cdx6500IBM2260sCallMnem
cdx6500IBM2260sCallMnem.description: This mnemonic name is used if this port is configured for originating connection requests.

cdx6500IBM2260sStationEnable.name: cdx6500IBM2260sStationEnable
cdx6500IBM2260sStationEnable.description: This parameter is used to disable/enable a station.
